Preconditions:
The input array `points` must not be null.
The input array `points` must contain at least three points.
Each point in the input array `points` must be an array of size 2, representing the x and y coordinates respectively.
The x and y coordinates of each point in the input array `points` must be within a valid range.

Postconditions:
The method should return a double value representing the area of the largest triangle that can be formed by any three different points.
The returned area value should be within a range of 10^-5 of the actual answer.